ObjectProperty.description: a tautoligical property indicating that the object is an entry as stored in a database. Its use is to indicate to implementors who are using high level entity types, as to the nature of the content of the entry i.e. the archetype

ObjectProperty.name: has discharge method
ObjectProperty.description: ponts to the method of discharge of the patient

ObjectProperty.name: is subsidiary to
ObjectProperty.description: An entity is subsidiary to another entity e,g, subencounter or subcomponent

ObjectProperty.name: has crud operation
ObjectProperty.description: create read update and delete operations to the data store

ObjectProperty.name: has attendance outcome
ObjectProperty.description: points to the outcome of the attendance

ObjectProperty.name: was generated by
ObjectProperty.description: An entity was generated by a provenance activity

ObjectProperty.name: has admission method
ObjectProperty.description: Points to the method of admission such as whether from waiting list, booked or from A&e or direct from GP

ObjectProperty.name: is process
ObjectProperty.description: points to a type of care administration process such as an admission discharge or administration note

ObjectProperty.name: has arrival mode
ObjectProperty.description: points to the mode of arrival in accident and emergency

ObjectProperty.name: operates within the sector of
ObjectProperty.description: Indicates which sector the speciality works in

ObjectProperty.name: has participants
ObjectProperty.description: The type of people the encounter took place between e.g. the patient and health professiona;, third party and health professional, team etc

ObjectProperty.name: has admission classification of patient
ObjectProperty.description: Points to the admissin classification of a patient e.g. elective day admission or non elective ordinay admission of maternity

ObjectProperty.name: has provenance
ObjectProperty.description: references the provenence of an entry i.e the history of the entry or its contents going back to its original creation

ObjectProperty.name: has subsidiary
ObjectProperty.description: An entity has subsidary entities such as a subencounter or care episode

ObjectProperty.name: has admission source
ObjectProperty.description: Points to the source of admission of the patient

ObjectProperty.name: has care event type
ObjectProperty.description: Points to the overall or main nature of the entry, usually a business process or observable concept of some kind e.g. an Encounter -> type -> Telephone consultation, or observation ->type-> Chest pain

ObjectProperty.name: is data model object field
ObjectProperty.description: A property that would be used in the data store  as a table field) as opposed to a property that is part of the definition of the class and points to an object (concept) or other entity (foreign key)

ObjectProperty.name: has data controller
ObjectProperty.description: references the organisation that is the data controller of the record entry (or sub organisation of that data controller)

ObjectProperty.name: has activity type
ObjectProperty.description: references the type of activity that occurred with the activity e.g. update of a data entry, delete or transformation

ObjectProperty.name: was performed by
ObjectProperty.description: references the person or device that performed the activity,usually used in provvenance

ObjectProperty.name: has event type of
ObjectProperty.description: references the concept that describes the type of event

ObjectProperty.name: has attendance status
ObjectProperty.description: points to whether the patient attended or not

DataProperty.name: has date of birth
DataProperty.description: Date of birth of person

DataProperty.name: has component date
DataProperty.description: the date and time of the creation or update to the component

DataProperty.name: date time property
DataProperty.description: A data property that has a date and time as a value

DataProperty.name: has Date and time of entry
DataProperty.description: A date and time a particular entry or component was made (local time)

DataProperty.name: has activity time
DataProperty.description: date and time of activity

DataProperty.name: id
DataProperty.description: A logical entity id usually an integer or uuid

DataProperty.name: start date/time
DataProperty.description: The effective start date and time relevant to the event being described (and not related to the entry date into the system)

DataProperty.name: has transaction number
DataProperty.description: An incremental integer for a transaction of some kind

DataProperty.name: has report identifier
DataProperty.description: the identifier of the report

DataProperty.name: has update time
DataProperty.description: date and time of the update

DataProperty.name: is data model data field
DataProperty.description: indicates that this property would be expected to be implmented as a field in a database or attribute within the data store, as opposed to a definitional property in the knowledge base. It has a simple data type as a value

DataProperty.name: has status
DataProperty.description: status of component

DataProperty.name: has description
DataProperty.description: description of object property or class

DataProperty.name: Annotation property
DataProperty.description: a property used in the information model of annotating classes

DataProperty.name: has iri
DataProperty.description: property that has a universal identifier as its value, reserved property

DataProperty.name: boolean property
DataProperty.description: A data property that has a true false value

DataProperty.name: has code
DataProperty.description: A code from an external taxonomy

DataProperty.name: has code prefix
DataProperty.description: prefix for a code for a code scheme or model

DataProperty.name: end date/time
DataProperty.description: the effective end date/time relevant to the event being described

DataProperty.name: integer property
DataProperty.description: A property that has an integer value

DataProperty.name: text property
DataProperty.description: A data property that has a text value

DataProperty.name: is data model entity
DataProperty.description: a significant property, that indicates that the objects of the class would be instantiated as entities within the record database as opposed to the knowledge base e.g. a table or resource or table+ type field.

DataProperty.name: Code
DataProperty.description: A text that is normally a code created for the purposes of categorising values

DataProperty.name: numeric property
DataProperty.description: A data property that has a floating point value

DataProperty.name: has ods code
DataProperty.description: a code for an organisation or person within the NHS social care sector

DataProperty.name: has resource Location
DataProperty.description: the location (implementation specific identifier) for a location e.g UUID or domain URI etc

DataProperty.name: has report name
DataProperty.description: a name of a report

DataProperty.name: has name
DataProperty.description: The name property of a concept or other structure

DataProperty.name: code property
DataProperty.description: A property that has a code as its value

DataProperty.name: has term for client
DataProperty.description: The organisations term for a client
